Description:
[recto] [Arthur M.] Hind, [= Early Italian engraving. A critical catalogue with complete reproduction of all the prints described], II, [London: Quaritch, 1938] p. 556;

  1. MORGANI (Printer, Florence about 1490-97) Carnesciale contrasto di Carnevale e la Quaresima, n.d. [...], [Paul] KRISTELLER, Early Florentine woodcuts [with an annotated list of Florentine illustrated books, London: Kegan Paul, Trench, Trübner and Co.], 1897, und Abbildung N° 85, weitere wichtige Holzschnittes, Fig. 69 dort auch abgeb. Fig 68, 176;
  2. See also Lorenzo de' Medici and others, Canzone per andare in maschera per Carnesciale fatte da piu persone, Morgiani e Petri, Florence n.d. (about 1493-97);
  3. see also: Literature on Carnival & Lent, esp. Netherlands;
  4. London, Brit.Mus., [A. W. Pollard, et al. (ed.)], Catalogue of books printed in the XV cent. [now in the British Museum], VI, [London: British Museum], (1930) Italy: Foligno, Ferrara, Florence, etc.;
  5. Gesamtkatalog der Wiegendrücke, vol. VII, [Leipzig : Verlag von Karl W. Hiersemann, 1925-1940] p. 33, 7460;
    [verso]
  6. Olschki, Leo S., Le Livre illustré au XVe S. Florence [Olschki],1926;
  7. Glück [sic];
  8. Tolnay: a) Zeichungen,[1925] b) Pierre Bruegel, l'Ancien, Bruxelles [Nouvelle société d'éditions],1935; Robert PROCTOR, An index to the early printed books in the B.M. [British Museum. From the invention of printing to the year 1500, With notes of those in the Bodleian Library to the year 1500, London: K. Paul, Trench, Trübner],1898-1903;
    [Walter Arthur] Copinger, Supplement to Hain's Repertorium [bibliographicum], [London: Henry Sotheran and Co.],1895-1902;
    To be discussed: The literary (and art) form of contrast;
    W. [Wilhelm] Creizenach, Geschichte des neueren Dramas, I, [Halle a.S.: Niemeyer, 1893], [pp.] 475-476.
